        "subject": "LU-3401 tests: make sanity test_27z robust and verbose",
        "message": "LU-3401 tests: make sanity test_27z robust and verbose\n\n* do not depend on positional parameters for most output\n* use \"lfs getstripe [-c|-i|-s]\" options to get specific values\n* parse OST index/objid/seq on a line-by-line basis\n* dispaly more infomation in error messages\n\nTest-Parameters: envdefinitions=SLOW=yes,ENABLE_QUOTA=yes clientdistro=el6 serverdistro=el6 clientarch=x86_64 serverarch=x86_64 serverjobs=lustre-master serverbuildno=1508 testlist=sanity\nSigned-off-by: Bobi Jam <bobijam.xu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iaf4bbd30a1f9c3bf47d634ddc5e122de60a25776\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/6468\nTested-by: Hudson\nTested-by: Maloo <whamcloud.maloo@gmail.com>\nReviewed-by: Lai Siyao <lai.siyao@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
